citeinfo.title: Generalized Land Ownership, Lake County, Minnesota

descript.abstract:
This layer represents land ownership in the following categories: county fee, tax forfeit, state, federal, municipal, private and tribal. The addition of the following county and state administrative subcategories is in-progress: county highway department, MN Dept. of Natural Resources, MN Dept. of Transportation, public school lands, school trust lands, and University of Minnesota Board of Regents.
Three cities (Beaver Bay, Silver Bay and Two Harbors) maintain their own tax parcels; this city data is represented as provided by the cities to the county.
descript.purpose: This layer represents generalized land ownership as well as several administrative subcategories.

Three cities (Beaver Bay, Silver Bay and Two Harbors) maintain their own tax parcels, and this city data is represented as received by the county.
Lake County also used data provided by the Minnesota Department of Natural Resources and the U.S. Forest Service.
